properties.areaDesc: West Slopes South Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 10 at 3:45AM PST until January 11 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow expected above 2000 feet. Total snow
accumulations of 6 to 18 inches above 2000 feet and 18 to 30
inches above 3000 feet. Light accumulations between 1 and 6
inches are possible between 1000 and 2000 feet.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Whatcom and Skagit
Counties, including Mount Baker Ski Area, Cascade mountains
and valleys of Snohomish and King Counties, including Index,
Skykomish, Stevens Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass and Cascade
mountains and valleys of Pierce and Lewis Counties, including
the Crystal Mountain Ski Area, Paradise on Mount Rainier.

* WHEN...From 4 AM Friday to 10 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to impossible.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The Northwest Avalanche Center expects
dangerous to very dangerous avalanche conditions Friday and
lingering through the weekend. Check nwac.us for the latest
avalanche forecast and conditions.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST SATURDAY ABOVE 2000 FEET
